Nike Popoola The Coalition Against COVID-19 on Wednesday donated a 100-bed isolation centre to Osun State Government as part of efforts to complement the fight against coronavirus pandemic in the state. Osun State Governor, Mr Gboyega Oyetola, who inaugurated the facility, after it was handed over by the Coordinator of CACOVID in the state, Dr Timothy Arowoogun, lauded the corporate social responsibility efforts of the group in supporting the government to mitigate the effects of the pandemic. He said CACOVID renovated the health facility and donated equipment and consumables for 100 beds to which the state government added 60 beds. Oyetola added that the state had another 20-room single beds isolation centre, giving the Mercyland facility a 180-bed isolation centre. He disclosed that the facility would serve as an addition to the governmentâ€™s other initiatives in containing the spread of the rampaging virus. He attributed the successes recorded by the state in the effective management of the pandemic to holistic approach launched against the virus since it commenced in Nigeria and the state. According to him, the state government has renovated and equipped a number of other isolation centres such as a 130-bed facility in Ejigbo; 12-bed capacity in Obafemi Awolowo University, Ile-Ife, a 20-bed isolation centre and eight-bed Intensive Care Unit at the State Specialist Hospital, Asubiaro, Osogbo, making 342-isolation beds and eight ICU-bed facility in the state. Copyright PUNCH.
